        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-12-02T23:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-12-02T23:56:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <head>257. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d257fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                        AGR 1 INDIA. Secret; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_FOL1">Freeman</persName>. The telegram
                        bears a handwritten notation that reads: “OK/L,” indicating that it was
                        cleared with the President. <persName corresp="#p_CCSJ1">Coon</persName> and
                        Sober were informed.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-12-02T23:56:00-05:00">December 2, 1965, 11:56 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>976. For Ambassador from Secretary Freeman. Please communicate to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SC1">Subramaniam</persName> that I have reviewed our Rome
                    agreement with the President who is pleased with the steps taken and
                    contemplated by the Indian Government to strengthen Indian agriculture. The
                    President looks forward to <persName corresp="#p_SC1">Subramaniam</persName>’s
                    outlining his program including points agreed upon at Rome publicly as soon as
                    possible, perhaps when he addresses Council of State as he suggested at Rome he
                    would do soon.<note n="2" xml:id="d257fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCA1">Bowles</persName> reported on December 3 that he
                        had conveyed this message to <persName corresp="#p_SC1"
                            >Subramaniam</persName> who indicated that he intended to present his
                        proposals for agricultural reform to the Cabinet and expected its approval.
                        (Telegram 1413 from New Delhi; ibid.)</note> Decision of <gloss
                        target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>–480, both extension period and amount, and
                    fertilizer loan under active consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
